issue.title: Model with multiple inputs in ONNXRuntime C++

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Hello guys, how can I run a model that uses multiple inputs? The ONNX Runtime C++ API has examples only for 1 input ( `auto output_tensors = session.Run(Ort::RunOptions{ nullptr }, input_node_names.data(), &input_tensor, 1, output_node_names.data(), 1);
`) . How can I do this?  Again, thanks for the help!

body:
@doruime : Your comments "Using OrtValue* input_tensors[input_node_names_.size()] works fine.
OrtRun(....,(const OrtValue* const*)&input_tensors,.....)" makes me confused. input_tensors is an array of OrtValue*, so it should be of type OrtValue**, so &input_tensors is of type OrtValue***, how can we force convert it into a (const OrtValue* const*)?
